		{
			"_id":"RsehlFqkNMv2LUdp",
			"name":"Attack",
			"type":"power",
			"img":"modules/dnd-4e-compendium/icons/powers/simple_personal.png",
			"effects":[],
			"folder":null,
			"sort":0,
			"flags":{},
			"system":{
				"description":{
					"value":"<p><b>Standard Action</b></p><p><b>Melee</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Target: </b> Each creature even with or west of the easternmost open hatch.</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Attack in rounds 2 and 3: </b>+5 vs. Fortitude; the target slides 2 squares due west.</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Attack in rounds 4 and 5: </b>+7 vs. Fortitude; the target slides 4 squares due west.</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Attack in rounds 6 and 7: </b>+9 vs. Fortitude, the target slides 6 squares due west.</p><p>Effect All squares between the easternmost open hatches and the crevasse are difficult terrain.</p><p>Effect Creatures pushed into the crevasse are buried in sand up to their waist and are restrained (save at -2 penalty ends).</p>",
